summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 24045, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller of the City of Seattle to execute an indemnity bond to the United States of America in the sum of Twenty-seven and 21/100 ($27.21) dollars to serve as a guarantee against the duplicate payment of a bank check in a like sum which was draw by the Quartermaster's Department in favor of the City of Seattle for electric current used at Pier No. 5, City of Seattle, during the month of November, 1909", approved May 9, 1910.
